Global Scalp Clips market size was valued at USD 46.24 million in 2025. The market is projected to grow from USD 46.24 million in 2026 to USD 82.17 million by 2034, exhibiting a CAGR of 8.8% during the forecast period.
Scalp clips are medical devices designed to keep the surgical area clean and sterile during operative procedures. The primary components consist of the metal or polymer clip itself and an outer protective shell that ensures secure placement on the scalp while minimizing tissue trauma.
